#ROOM
Vnum     11300
Name     &rThe Ragefire Entrance&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The temperature here is noticeably higher than in the Cleft of Shadow
above. The air is thick with the scent of sulfur and parched earth.
Crude obsidian steps lead down into the volcanic fissures that run
deep beneath Orgrimmar. A shimmering, orange portal hums with power,
separating the city from the dangerous depths.
~
#EXIT
Direction out~
ToRoom    11298
Desc      Return to the Cleft of Shadow.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction down~
ToRoom    11301
Desc      Descend deeper into the chasm.~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11301
Name     &rThe Jagged Path&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     This narrow tunnel is carved directly into the dark, volcanic rock.
Small fissures in the walls emit a faint, red glow from the magma
churning far below. Footprints of heavy, three-toed creatures are
visible in the thick dust.
~
#EXIT
Direction up~
ToRoom    11300
Desc      The entrance portal.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11302
Desc      The path continues south.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 11300 10 11301
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11302
Name     &rThe Jagged Path - Bend&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The tunnel turns sharply here, opening into a wider passage. The
sound of rhythmic chanting and the clatter of stone on stone echo
from the east. Crude trogg trophies—skulls and bird feathers—hang
from the jagged ceiling.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11301
Desc      The path back to the entrance.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    11303
Desc      The path leads toward a wider cavern.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 11300 10 11302
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11303
Name     &rThe Trogg Tunnels - Entrance&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The cavern widens here, revealing a network of tunnels claimed by
the Ragefire troggs. The walls are stained with soot from primitive
braziers. To the north and south, smaller alcoves serve as living
quarters for the primal dwellers.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11304
Desc      A small side cavern.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11305
Desc      A small side cavern.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    11306
Desc      The main trogg corridor.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    11302
Desc      The jagged bend.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 11300 10 11303
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11304
Name     &rTrogg Dwelling - North&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     This small alcove is filled with piles of moldy fur and gnawed bones.
The smell of unwashed trogg is nearly overwhelming in the cramped
space.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11303
Desc      The entrance cavern.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 11300 10 11304
Reset O 0 11300 5 11304
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11305
Name     &rTrogg Dwelling - South&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     Several primitive stone tools lie scattered across the floor here.
A small pile of glowing coals in the center of the room provides a
dim, flickering light.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11303
Desc      The entrance cavern.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 11301 10 11305
  Reset G 1 11301 10
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11306
Name     &rThe Main Trogg Corridor&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     This high-ceilinged corridor is the primary artery of the trogg
territory. Several trogg warriors stand guard here, their low grunts
echoing off the obsidian walls. To the east, the corridor opens into
a massive, multi-tiered chamber.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    11307
Desc      The central trogg chamber.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    11303
Desc      The entrance cavern.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 11300 10 11306
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11307
Name     &rThe Central Trogg Chamber&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     This immense natural cavern serves as the heart of the Ragefire
tribe. Stone platforms have been carved into the walls, connected
by rickety wooden walkways. In the center, a large fire pit burns
constantly, casting long, dancing shadows across the rock.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11308
Desc      A path leading to the upper tiers.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11309
Desc      A path leading to the lower tiers.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    11306
Desc      The main corridor.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 11300 10 11307
Reset M 0 11301 10 11307
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11308
Name     &rTrogg Tunnels - Upper Tier&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     From this vantage point, you can look down upon the central fire
pit of the trogg chamber. The air is thinner and hotter here, as 
the tunnel climbs toward a dead end.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11307
Desc      The central chamber.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    11311
Desc      Oggleflint's Crag.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 11300 10 11308
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11309
Name     &rTrogg Tunnels - Lower Tier&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The ground slopes downward, leading away from the trogg dwellings
and toward the subterranean river of lava. The rock beneath your
feet feels uncomfortably warm.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11307
Desc      The central chamber.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11310
Desc      The descent to the Searing Chasm.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 11300 10 11309
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11310
Name     &rThe descent to the Searing Chasm&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The sound of rushing lava becomes a constant roar as you descend
this steep, narrow tunnel. The air is shimmering with heat, and
sweat begins to pour down your face. The troggs seem to avoid this
area, fearing the elementals below.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11309
Desc      The lower trogg tier.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction down~
ToRoom    11312
Desc      The entrance to the Searing Chasm.~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11311
Name     &rOggleflint's Crag&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     This elevated crag overlooks the entire trogg village. It is the
most defensible position in the upper chasm, occupied by the leader
of the Ragefire tribe. A massive, blood-stained bone rests against
the back wall.
~
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    11308
Desc      The upper tier.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 11304 1 11311
  Reset E 1 11303 1 16
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11312
Name     &ROverlook of the Searing Chasm&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     You stand on a high ledge overlooking a spectacular and terrifying
vista. A wide river of molten rock flows through the center of a
massive cavern, illuminating the darkness with a violent, orange
glare. Pillars of basalt rise from the magma like the teeth of some
ancient beast.
~
#EXIT
Direction up~
ToRoom    11310
Desc      The path back to the trogg tunnels.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction down~
ToRoom    11313
Desc      Descend to the floor of the chasm.~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11313
Name     &RThe Chasm Floor - North&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The heat here is nearly suffocating. The rock floor is cracked and
bubbling in places, revealing the lava just inches beneath the
surface. Strange, flickering spirits of flame drift through the air,
guarding the elemental heart of the chasm.
~
#EXIT
Direction up~
ToRoom    11312
Desc      The overlook ledge.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11314
Desc      The floor of the chasm continues south.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 11302 10 11313
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11314
Name     &RThe Chasm Floor - Central&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     In the center of this volcanic hall, the heat is at its most
intense. To the east and west, narrow paths lead around the 
central lava pool. The air is thick with ash and the smell of
burning minerals.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11313
Desc      The northern floor.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    11315
Desc      The eastern path.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11316
Desc      The southern floor.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    11317
Desc      The western path.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 11302 10 11314
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11315
Name     &RThe Searing Path - East&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     A narrow ledge of rock skirts the edge of the lava pool. The
magma bubbles and pops just a few feet away, occasionally splashing
the path with liquid fire.
~
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    11314
Desc      The central floor.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 11302 10 11315
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11316
Name     &RThe Chasm Floor - South&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The volcanic activity seems slightly more stable here. The floor
is solid rock, though still incredibly hot. To the south, the 
cavern narrows into a series of jagged tunnels.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11314
Desc      The central floor.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11318
Desc      The southern tunnels.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 11302 10 11316
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11317
Name     &RThe Searing Path - West&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     This path is precarious, requiring careful footwork to avoid the
many fissures that lead directly into the molten depths. A small
cave entrance is visible to the west.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    11314
Desc      The central floor.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    11326
Desc      Maur Grimtotem's Outlook.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 11302 10 11317
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11318
Name     &rThe Shadow Council Outpost - Entry&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The natural rock has been reinforced here with heavy, iron-bound
timbers. Purple silk banners emblazoned with the symbol of the
Shadow Council hang from the walls. The primal, volcanic heat is
replaced by a chilling, magical cold.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11316
Desc      The Searing Chasm.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11319
Desc      The outpost corridor.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 11306 1 11318
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11319
Name     &rShadow Council Corridor - North&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     Orc warlocks in dark robes pace this hallway, chanting in the
forgotten tongue of the Eredar. The air vibrates with the hum of
contained demonic energy. To the east and west, small rooms have 
been carved out for dark rituals.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11318
Desc      The outpost entry.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    11320
Desc      A ritual chamber.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11321
Desc      The corridor continues south.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    11322
Desc      A ritual chamber.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 11306 1 11319
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11320
Name     &rRitual Chamber of Shadow&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     A large, circular seal has been painted on the floor in dried
blood. Several black candles burn with a flickering, purple flame,
casting long, distorted shadows against the jagged walls.
~
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    11319
Desc      The northern corridor.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 11306 1 11320
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11321
Name     &rShadow Council Corridor - South&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The corridor widens as it approaches the lower sanctum. Massive
iron chains hang from the ceiling, their purpose unknown but 
ominous. The sound of a deep, demonic roar echoes from the south.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11319
Desc      The northern corridor.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11336
Desc      The Shadow Council Sanctum.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 11306 1 11321
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11322
Name     &rRitual Chamber of Flame&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The air in this room is thick with smoke. An obsidian altar sits
against the far wall, covered in strange, glowing runes. It seems
the Shadow Council is attempting to bind the volcanic fire to their
own dark purposes.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    11319
Desc      The northern corridor.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 11306 1 11322
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11326
Name     &RMaur Grimtotem's Outlook&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     This secluded cave offers a quiet sanctuary from the roaring lava
outside. It is sparsely furnished with a single bedroll and a small
stone table. Maur Grimtotem stands here, watching the bubbling
magma with a grim expression.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    11317
Desc      The western path.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 11305 1 11326
  Reset G 1 11304 1
  Reset G 1 11306 1
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11327
Name     &rThe Earthborer Tunnels - Entry&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     Branching off from the searing heat, these tunnels are damp and
cool. The walls are smooth, as if melted by a powerful acid or
ground down by some massive creature. To the east, the tunnel
slopes downward into the dark.
~
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    11307
Desc      The central trogg chamber.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    11328
Desc      The worm tunnels.~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11328
Name     &rEarthborer Tunnel - Slant&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The ground is covered in a sticky, translucent slime that makes
movement difficult. To the north and south, smaller burrows lead
into the solid rock, likely the nests of the giant worms that
inhabit this area.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11329
Desc      A small burrow.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    11330
Desc      A small burrow.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    11327
Desc      The entry tunnel.~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    11331
Desc      The tunnels continue east.~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 11303 10 11328
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     11329
Name     &rEarthborer Nest - North&d~
Sector   underground~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The walls here are lined with segmented shells and discarded
mandibles. The smell of decay is strong, as if this burrow is used
to store food for the swarm.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
